<subSubSection id="C30307BDE8125867F810A26FE21BF6E4" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA65436E8125867F810A26FE21BF6E4" blockId="2.[1995,2581,1967,2396]" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">
The “Syrian 
<taxonomicName id="4C192FB5E8125867F75FA26FE3BFF7B8" box="[2180,2284,2126,2159]" class="Mammalia" family="Equidae" genus="Equus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="onager">Onager</taxonomicName>
” 
<taxonomicName id="4C192FB5E8125867F6D1A26FE206F741" authority="(Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1855)" baseAuthorityName="Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" baseAuthorityYear="1855" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="hemippus">race hemippus (Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire, 1855)</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F30E14A6E8125867F609A254E146F741" box="[2514,2581,2165,2198]" name="Syria" pageId="2" pageNumber="139">Syria</collectingCountry>
and the Arabian Peninsula is extinct. The “Gobi Kulan” luteus is probably a synonym of the nominate 
<taxonomicName id="4C192FB5E8125867F71DA2CAE2DBF6DB" box="[2246,2440,2283,2316]" class="Mammalia" family="Equidae" genus="Equus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perissodactyla" pageId="2" pageNumber="139" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="hemionus" subSpecies="hemionus">race hemionus</taxonomicName>
. Four extant subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
